Here is the fixed syntax:

```
return (
  <div className={styles.container}>
    <img
      className={styles.image}
      src={sampleDiningHall.imageUrl}
      alt={sampleDiningHall.name}
    />
    <h1 className={styles.title}>{sampleDiningHall.name}</h1>
    <Link href={`/newReview/${id}`}>
      <a className={styles.addReview}>Add a review</a>
     </Link>
    <h2>Reviews</h2>
    {sampleReviews.map((review, i) => (
      <ReviewCard key={i} {...review} />
    ))}
  </div>
);
```

In this code, the syntax error is in the `Link` component where the curly braces are missing around the URL. It has been fixed by adding the curly braces and enclosing the URL in backticks and quotes inside the `href` attribute: 

```
<Link href={`/newReview/${id}`}>
``` 

Additionally, the dot (`...`) in the `ReviewCard` component is invalid syntax and should be replaced by a spread operator (`...`).

please fix this syntax:   return (
    <div>
